    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fluorescent lamps, available in two types, with ultraviolet emitting phosphors. Used in the ultraviolet investigation of cultural materials, conservation, and in many scientific contexts. Filtered black light blue bulbs produce a dark violet glow with phosphors releasing near 404.7 nm; non-filtered black light bulbs emit a light blue light with phosphors releasing near 360 nm.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000053102/Liscum and Briggs, Mutations in the NPH1 Locus of Arabidopsis, The Plant Cell (1995)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000053103/Jennings and Pocock, Relationships between Sensitivity to Agricultural Intensification and Ecological Traits, Conservation Biology (2009)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000114707/Oxford English Dictionary Online (2002-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fluorescerende lampen, beschikbaar in twee soorten, met fosforescerende stoffen die ultraviolet licht uitstralen. Gebruikt voor het met ultraviolet licht onderzoeken van voorwerpen en voor een groot aantal wetenschappelijke experimenten. Zwarte lampen met filters produceren donkerviolet licht met een golflengte van rond de 404,7 nm. Zwarte lampen zonder filter produceren lichtblauw licht met een golflengte van rond de 360 nm.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>具紫外線的螢光燈。由於紫外線可釋出磷光體，因此該燈泡可用於文化物質與多種科學實驗的紫外線探測上；其型態可分為兩種，有濾光功能之黑光藍燈泡會發出深紫光，所釋放的磷光體將近404.7納米，不具濾光功能之黑光燈泡則發出淺藍光，所釋放的磷光體將近360納米。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
